  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "So in the light of these challenges, how are the current AI developments making an industrial impact?The current wave of AI developments has centred around so-called Generative AI methods and Large Language Models (LLMs).",
    "Generative AI broadly refers to creating new content such as text, video, audio based on previously trained data patterns and LLMs is a subset focused on text content creation.",
    "A key breakthrough has been the ability to interpret, numerically codify and manipulate human language-so-called Natural Language Processing or NLP.",
    "In their simplest operations, these models provide the ability to automatically process existing information or knowledge, access new information, organize information and combine information to address requests for reports, synopses, surveys and other data structures.",
    "In an industrial context, there are many opportunities for using LLMs for efficiency gains and labour time saving.By way of illustration at a recent Industrial Advisory Board meeting of the Made Smart Centre for Connected Factories [6] industrial collaborators identified areas where simple LLM applications are beginning to be used industrially such as work instructions, data sheet preparation, employee navigation systems while identifying near term opportunities in reporting, human resource information provision, inspection and CNC programming.The immediate attraction of the generative AI deployment examples just outlined is that they avoid the four challenge areas listed above: Because they are not being directly applied to production operations in these examples, many of the digital maturity issues with Challenge 1 do not apply."
  ],
